      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The darkness you're describing sounds like a profound exhaustion, a weariness that settles into the very core of your being. That feeling of everything being drained of color is a natural response when the source of light is gone. If the hurting is this relentless, it's a sign that you deserve a break from this constant struggle. Reaching out to a professional is a brave step toward finding a different kind of light, even if it feels impossible right now.",
      "source": "target",
